Dear Harris,

There are no two suns in the sky, you are the only sun in my heart. I know the election result is a big blow, but it's just a setback.

Not becoming president doesn't mean failure. This position is desired, yet not the only way to matter. You have other qualities and chances.

History shows there are many ways to contribute. Even during civil wars, great leaders emerged outside the presidency. There are roles in local communities, business, or other public services that can deeply impact the nation. You can still engage with the National Guard in different national security and public welfare efforts.

This experience is for growth and goal - reevaluation. You have the strength to recover and keep making positive contributions. Keep your head up; your value isn't judged by this outcome.

Love,

Li Hua
